  "body": "* viper Version: 0.0.2\r\n* OS: linux\r\n* Python Version (python --version): 3.6.1\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe following three do *not* agree on the value range of type`num`.\r\n\r\n1. The [doc](https://viper.readthedocs.io/en/latest/types.html) says: `num` = [-2\\*\\*127+1, 2\\*\\*127-2]\r\n> ``num``:  equivalent to``int128``, a signed integer strictly between -2\\*\\*127 and 2\\*\\*127-1.\r\n\r\n2. `clamp` accepts [-2\\*\\*127, 2\\*\\*127-1]\r\n\r\n```\r\ndef foo():\r\n    one = 1\r\n    x =  170141183460469231731687303715884105726 + one #  2**127 - 1\r\n    z = -170141183460469231731687303715884105727 - one # -2**127\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Viper compiler accepts [-2\\*\\*127+1, 2\\*\\*127-1]\r\n\r\nFor the following program:\r\n```\r\ndef foo():\r\n    x =  170141183460469231731687303715884105727 #  2**127 - 1\r\n    y = -170141183460469231731687303715884105727 # -2**127 + 1\r\n    z = -170141183460469231731687303715884105728 # -2**127\r\n```\r\nViper compiler complained:\r\n```\r\nline 4: Number out of range: 170141183460469231731687303715884105728\r\n    z = -170141183460469231731687303715884105728 # -2**127\r\n---------^\r\n```\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nIdentify the correct behavior out of the three, and fix the other two.\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n\r\n```\r\no                  o             o                  o\r\n  o ___/|__          o            o   o              o\r\no _/       \\  /| o              o     ___/|__      o\r\n /  @ \\\\    \\/ |    o            o  _/       \\  /|   o  ___/|__\r\n \\_   //    /\\ |  o  ___/|__       /  @ \\\\    \\/ | o  _/       \\  /|\r\n   \\_______/  \\| o _/       \\  /|  \\_   //    /\\ |  o/  @ \\\\    \\/ |\r\n                  /  @ \\\\    \\/ |    \\_______/  \\|   \\_   //    /\\ |\r\n                  \\_   //    /\\ |                      \\_______/  \\|\r\n                    \\_______/  \\| \r\n```",
